title: Youth unemployment rate in Egypt in 2019
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Youth unemployment rate. In total the number of data points it has is 21.
In general Youth unemployment rate has rose over the Year.
The steepest decrease occurs in between the Year 2006 and 2007.
The highest Youth unemployment rate, of value 34.68 was reached at Year 2015
Minimum Youth unemployment rate about 20.13 was reached at Year 1999
